Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @Potatoes{3}(chopped) into 2cm thick wedges (peeling optional). Pop the wedges onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @Oil{to taste}. Season with @Salt{to taste}, @Pepper{to taste} and @Harissa Spice Mix{1%sachet}.

Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer.

Once oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary—you want the wedges nicely spread out!

Meanwhile, quarter the @Cherry Tomatoes{250%grams}(quartered).

Finely chop the @Parsley{5%grams}(finely chopped) (stalks and all).

Peel and grate the @Garlic{1%clove}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #medium bowl{}, mix the @Red Wine Vinegar{1%sachet} with @Oil{2%tbsp}. Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste} then add the parsley and tomatoes.

Just before serving, add the @Salad Leaves{40%grams} to the bowl and toss to coat.

Add half the @Harissa Paste{1%sachet} to a #small bowl{} along with the @Aioli{1%sachet}.

Mix together then set aside.

When 15 mins of cooking time remain for the wedges, place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, fry the @Chorizo{100%grams} until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the chorizo from the pan and mix with the remaining harissa paste.

Return the pan to medium-high heat (add a drizzle of oil if the pan is too dry).

Roughly chop the @Prawns{180%grams}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Once the pan is hot, add the prawns.

Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste} and fry, stirring, for ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside.

Meanwhile, pop the @Tortilla{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Top the tortillas with harissa chorizo chunks and fried prawns.

Garnish each taco with the rocket and tomato salad.

Finish with a drizzle of harissa aioli.

Serve with the spiced wedges alongside.